    <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Disabilities can be permanent, temporary or situational</h2>
    <p class="govuk-body">At least <a href="https://www.scope.org.uk/media/disability-facts-figures" class="govuk-link">1 in 5 people in the UK have a long term illness, impairment or disability. Many more have a temporary disability.</a> Many more have a temporary disability.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">Someone’s ability to use a service could be affected many ways and may be permanent , temporary or situational . Understanding this reinforces why we research, design and build services for everyone.
Even if you do not have disabled users currently using your service, it’s important that you do not put up barriers to people who might want to use it in future.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">Web accessibility is essential for people with disabilities and useful for all. Essential for some, useful for all.</p>
